{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Enforce release-source authorization + version lockstep before publication\n\nAdd a repository-enforced gate so the release workflow can only build and publish\nfrom a commit that is provably the reviewed-and-landed `main`, with the tag and all\nrelease manifests agreeing on the version, and production publication behind an\nindependently-approved environment. (Readiness Finding 1 — verified VALID against\n`release.yml:17-21`, `infra/terraform-github/main.tf:23-101`, `docs/releasing.md`.)\n\n## Why\n\n`main` is constrained to the Gerrit replication deploy key, but `refs/tags/v*` was\ndeliberately left open (`infra/terraform-github/main.tf:23-28`) so a human can push\na `v*` tag to drive PyPI + MCP-registry + GitHub-Release publication\n(`release.yml:17-21`, jobs `build`/`publish`/`github_release`/`mcp_registry`). The\nonly gate anywhere is `if: startsWith(github.ref, 'refs/tags/v')` — nothing checks\nthat the tagged SHA is an ancestor of (or equal to) reviewed `main`, verifies any\nGerrit/CI result for that exact SHA, or asserts version consistency. A PEP 740\nattestation would correctly name this repo's workflow but cannot distinguish a tag\non reviewed `main` from a tag on any other commit. Separately, the three version\nvalues (`pyproject.toml:10`, `server.json` top-level and `packages[].version`) are\nkept in lockstep only by a manual runbook (`docs/releasing.md`), so a future\nmismatch would publish disagreeing versions across the PyPI / GitHub-Release / MCP\nchannels with no machine check.\n\n## What\n\nAdopt the uv / pydantic release-integrity pattern (uv: `workflow_dispatch` +\ndedicated release-gate environment; pydantic: an explicit version-check step before\nbuild). Add a **source-authorization job** that runs before any OIDC-enabled job:\n\n- Resolve the release SHA explicitly and fetch the protected `main` ref.\n- Prove the release SHA is reachable from reviewed `main` per policy\n  (`git merge-base --is-ancestor \"$GITHUB_SHA\" origin/main`, or exact-equality to\n  the `main` tip if the project prefers).\n- Parse the tag and every manifest and assert exact equality **before build**:\n  `tag_without_v == project.version == server.json.version ==\n  each server.json.packages[].version`.\n- Make the `build` job `needs:` this gate and make `publish` depend on an\n  independently-approved deployment environment (required reviewers on the `pypi`\n  environment — an operator-side GitHub setting).\n- Restrict `refs/tags/v*` creation/update/deletion/force-update to a controlled\n  release identity via the GitHub ruleset in `infra/terraform-github/main.tf`.\n- Record the approved SHA, tag, manifest versions, and artifact hashes in release\n  evidence (e.g. a job summary / uploaded evidence file).\n\n## Scope\n\n- `.github/workflows/release.yml` — new `authorize-source` job; `build`/`publish`\n  gated on it; version-lockstep assertion step.\n- `infra/terraform-github/main.tf` — a `refs/tags/v*` ruleset restricting tag\n  writes to the release identity.\n- `docs/releasing.md` — document the gate and the required environment reviewers.\n  **Section ownership:** this story owns the \"Release-source authorization\" section;\n  Finding 3 owns the \"Build-once\" section and Finding 4 owns the \"Pinning\" section,\n  so the three concurrent release stories do not overlap-edit the same headings.\n- Out of scope: replacing the tag-triggered model with `workflow_dispatch`\n  entirely (keep the tag trigger; add the gate). Out of scope: the build-once /\n  pinning work (Findings 3 and 4 — separate stories that also touch `release.yml`;\n  coordinate ordering per the epic).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A `authorize-source` job resolves the release SHA, fetches `origin/main`, and\n  fails the run when the SHA is not reachable from `main` (demonstrated by\n  Experiment 1A: a tag on an off-main commit is rejected before any publish job).\n- [ ] A version-lockstep step asserts `tag_without_v`, `pyproject.toml` version,\n  `server.json` version, and every `server.json.packages[].version` are equal and\n  fails before build on any mismatch (demonstrated by Experiment 1B).\n- [ ] `build`, `publish`, `github_release`, and `mcp_registry` do not start unless\n  `authorize-source` succeeds (they `needs:` it, directly or transitively).\n- [ ] `infra/terraform-github/main.tf` defines a ruleset over `refs/tags/v*`\n  restricting tag create/update/delete to the release identity.\n- [ ] `docs/releasing.md` documents the authorization gate, the version-lockstep\n  invariant, and the environment-reviewer requirement.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] The live `pypi` GitHub environment has required reviewers\n  enabled so production publication needs an independent approval (attested by a\n  comment naming the environment settings screenshot/URL or an org-admin confirmation).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass, and the change lands via the\n  Gerrit two-vote gate."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784045843352126001,"uuid":"bac9d8cd-a8a8-40da-873a-f49ee04c2ef7"}